				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The PPU registers are mirrored all the way from $2000 to $3FFF. This means that writing to $2008 (for example) is the same as writing to $2000, so you shouldn't check for the exact addresses in your switch. Instead, check whether the address being accessed is in the $2000-$3FFF range, then discard all bits of the address except the first 3, which you can use to select a register (0 to 7).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

